Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 05 of Hand MRI
When I select 'Finding' radio button
Then Finding dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Ligament lesions of the fingers' from the dropdown menu
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'D1' radio button is enabled
And 'D2' radio button is enabled
And 'D3' radio button is enabled
And 'D4' radio button is enabled
And 'D5' radio button is enabled
And 'Suspicion of' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'D1' radio button
Then 'Annular pulley rupture' checkbox is enabled
And 'Tenosynovitis stenosans' checkbox is enabled
And 'Rupture of the extensor tendon' checkbox is enabled

And 'Ligamentum collaterale ulnare (LCU) metacarpo-phalangeal joint' radio button is enabled
And 'Ligamentum collaterale radial (LCR) metacarpophalangeal joint' radio button is enabled
And 'IP ulnar' radio button is enabled
And 'IP radial' radio button is enabled


When I select 'Annular pulley rupture' checkbox
Then 'A1' radio button is enabled
And 'O' radio button is enabled
And 'A2' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Tenosynovitis stenosans' checkbox
Then 'A1' radio button is enabled
And 'O' radio button is enabled
And 'A2' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Rupture of the extensor tendon' checkbox
Then 'Avulsion fracture' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Ligamentum collaterale ulnare (LCU) metacarpo-phalangeal joint' radio button
Then 'Strain' radio button is enabled
And 'Partial rupture' radio button is enabled
And 'Non-displaced complete rupture' radio button is enabled
And 'Displaced complete rupture (stener lesion)' radio button is enabled
When I select 'Displaced complete rupture (stener lesion)' radio button
Then 'Avulsion Injury' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Ligamentum collaterale radial (LCR) metacarpophalangeal joint' radio button
Then 'Strain' radio button is enabled
And 'Partial rupture' radio button is enabled
And 'Non-displaced complete rupture' radio button is enabled
And 'Displaced complete rupture' radio button is enabled
When I select 'Displaced complete rupture' radio button
Then 'Avulsion Injury' checkbox is enabled
